## Step 2: Create the API Client

Create `src/lib/api.ts` that talks to the FastAPI backend. Here is the exact API contract:

### `GET /api/health`
Returns: `{ status: "ok" }`

### `GET /api/models`
Returns:
```json
[
  { "id": "llama-3.1-8b-instant", "name": "Llama 3.1 8B Instant", "description": "Fast and efficient, great for most tasks" },
  { "id": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile", "name": "Llama 3.3 70B Versatile", "description": "Larger model, better reasoning and quality" },
  { "id": "mixtral-8x7b-32768", "name": "Mixtral 8x7B", "description": "Mixture-of-experts model with 32K context" }
]
```

### `POST /api/chat` (SSE Streaming)
Request body:
```json
{
  "messages": [{ "role": "user", "content": "Hello" }],
  "model": "llama-3.1-8b-instant",
  "temperature": 0.5,
  "system_prompt": "You are a helpful assistant."
}
```
Returns: Server-Sent Events stream. Each event is `data: <json>\n\n` where JSON is one of:
- `{ "token": "Hello", "done": false }` — a content chunk
- `{ "token": "", "done": true, "metadata": { "model": "...", "time": 1.23 } }` — stream complete
- `{ "error": "Rate limit reached..." }` — error

**Important:** Use `fetch()` with `AbortController` for cancellation. Parse the SSE stream manually (split on `\n\n`, parse `data: ` prefix).

### `GET /api/chats`
Returns: `[{ id, title, created_at, updated_at, message_count }]` sorted newest first

### `POST /api/chats`
Request: `{ "title": "New Chat" }` (optional)
Returns: `{ id, title, created_at, updated_at, message_count, messages: [] }`

### `GET /api/chats/{id}`
Returns: Full chat session with `messages` array

### `PUT /api/chats/{id}`
Request: `{ "title": "...", "messages": [...] }` (both optional)
Returns: Updated chat session

### `DELETE /api/chats/{id}`
Returns: `{ "status": "deleted", "id": "..." }`

