## Step 3: Create the SSE Streaming Hook

Create `src/hooks/useChat.ts`:
- Manages the current chat messages state
- `sendMessage(content: string)` — adds user message, calls `POST /api/chat` with SSE streaming
- Accumulates streamed tokens into an assistant message in real-time
- Supports `cancelStream()` using `AbortController`
- Tracks `isStreaming` state for UI feedback
- After stream completes, saves messages to backend via `PUT /api/chats/{id}`

---

## Step 4: Create the Chat Sessions Hook

Create `src/hooks/useChatSessions.ts`:
- `sessions` — list of all chat sessions (from `GET /api/chats`)
- `activeSessionId` — currently active chat
- `createSession()` — calls `POST /api/chats`, sets as active
- `loadSession(id)` — calls `GET /api/chats/{id}`, loads messages
- `deleteSession(id)` — calls `DELETE /api/chats/{id}`
- `renameSession(id, title)` — calls `PUT /api/chats/{id}`
- Auto-refreshes session list after mutations

